    "client_msg_id": "0841f461-3863-40dc-bc22-acf01205ffd2",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "all of Neil Postman’s books are great, my fav is Amusing Ourselves to Death.\n\nThe one caveat / bias I always have to remember though is that he has a very very strong point of view that’s very singular. To the point that I feel like its incomplete, so I would take every sentence with a grain of salt. I’ve forced myself to be more socratic and read ‘opposing’ views as well here. Tech + culture takes are always somewhat non-scientific (doesn’t mean they’re wrong, but like with reading nutrition takes…the value is in absorbing multiple opinions &amp; frameworks)",
